TCP ICMP Error Handling Demo
============================

Two configurations demonstrating TCP ICMP error handling.

Config HardError (Phase 2)
--------------------------
Network: client (StandardHost) <--Ethernet--> target (Router, no TCP)

The client tries to TCP-connect to a Router that has no TCP module.
The Router's IPv4 sends ICMP Protocol Unreachable (hard error).
TCP immediately reports CONNECTION_REFUSED instead of waiting for
the connection establishment timeout.

Config Pmtud (Phase 3)
----------------------
Network: client <--PPP (MTU 1500)--> router <--PPP (MTU 800)--> server

The client sends a large TCP stream to the server through a router
whose outgoing link has a smaller MTU (800 bytes).

Before Phase 3:
  TCP does not set the DF (Don't Fragment) bit. IPv4 silently
  fragments oversized packets at the router. No ICMP errors.

After Phase 3:
  TCP sets DF on all segments. The router sends ICMP Fragmentation
  Needed (Packet Too Big) with MTU=800. TCP reduces snd_mss and
  retransmits with smaller segments — no IP fragmentation needed.
